HEADWORD: Stull
<hw>Stull</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[CF.
<er>Stum</er>.]</ety> <def>A framework of timber covered with boards to
support rubbish; also, a framework of boards to protect miners from
falling stones.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

